news.title: Ludhiana civic body issues notices to shop tenants to clear property tax
news.para: ​He said they have served many notices to the defaulters and now they have served fresh notices, giving them a week to clear the outstanding dues or else the property will be sealed after another 3-day notice.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board awaits UT admin nod for auction of commercial properties
news.para: As soon as the CHB will secure the nod, it will put these properties that were in poor condition and had not found any takers for e-auction.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco hands over entire airport land, clears core area of 3,000 buildings
news.para: The entire airport land of around 1,160 hectares has been handed over to the developer, Adani Group, for the proposed second airport for Mumbai.

news.title: Mumbai: Builder arrested for duping flat buyers of 32 crore
news.para: ​​Accused Sachin Khanolkar (52) has been booked on charges of cheating and forgery. He and one Mayuresh Audegoankar are the directors of Siddhivinayak constructions which operates on the Parel-Dadar belt.

news.title: Gurugram: Labour department issues notice to AIPL over deaths at building site
news.para: Department officials, who visited the site for an inspection, sought the details of the three workers and asked the developer — Advance India Projects Limited (AIPL) — to compensate them in keeping with the guidelines.

news.title: Ghaziabad: CAG seeks details from GDA on encroachments, penalties & illegal buildings
news.para: It has also asked for details on action taken against illegal constructions, penalties imposed on such developers and the amount realised from defaulters during the period.

news.title: Mumbai: No HC relief, Ahuja Constructions' directors arrested in cheque-bouncing case
news.para: The duo was picked up from near the Bombay high court on Friday afternoon. Ahuja Constructions is known for its signature luxury projects in Central Mumbai and western suburbs.

news.title: U.S. mortgage rates jump again, buyers head to the sideline
news.para: Mortgage buyer Freddie Mac reported Thursday that the 30-year rate jumped to 5.23% this week from 5.09% last week. A year ago at this time, the average rate was 2.96%. Until April, the average rate hadn't exceeded 5% in more than a decade.

news.title: Property market buoyancy supports 34% jump in FY22 stamp duty collection
news.para: The average monthly revenue collection across these states and union territories during the financial year rose to R 14,262 crore as compared to Rs 10,646 crore in the previous year.

news.title: NCLAT begins insolvency proceedings in just one project of Supertech
news.para: A two-member NCLAT bench limited the Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) to only "Eco Village II Project" located at Greater Noida (West).

news.title: Visakhapatnam: CBI books infra firm, 10 others for Rs 5.72 crore SBI loan fraud
news.para: Navya Infracon Projects Private Limited, represented by its managing director and builder Manyam Vijaya Kumar, constructed a residential project ‘Gadiraju Empire’ in MVP Colony in the port city.

news.title: Vadodara civic body to build 1,255 houses for urban poor
news.para: These include two housing schemes in Bil, four in Bhayli and one in Sevasi. The civic body will spend Rs 112.74 crore on the projects.

news.title: Unicorns to take on lease 8.1 million sq ft office space in 2022-24: Report
news.para: "Unicorns are likely to lease an average of about 2.7 million sq feet of office space annually across 2022-24 across the top six cities, a three-fold increase from the preceding three years," Colliers India said in a statement.

news.title: Karnataka: Property registration, April-May revenues hit a new high
news.para: The state has witnessed 1.8 lakh property registrations in April and 1.96 lakh in May, according to the department of stamps and registration.

news.title: Gurugram deputy commissioner orders probe after AVL 36A buyers' allegations
news.para: Deputy commissioner formed a committee comprising sub-divisional-magistrate (SDM) and district town planner (DTP) to investigate the allegations and also check if there is any violation of provision of Affordable Housing policy in AVL36A.
